Makhura speaking at Kgosana s funeral in Tshwane Events Centre on Friday hailed the PAC stalwart as one of the great revolutionaries to have emerged in the country. We remember him for his bravery humility integrity and his ruthless ethics his critical mind and his consistency. He never wavered in his beliefs Makhura said.The premier said the current leader in government had a lot to learn from Kgosana about leading with humility.At the age of 23 Kgosana led more than 30 000 people in an anti-pass protest. He was arrested and tried for incitement but fled South Africa while he was out on bail.Kgosana was born in 1936 in Makapanstad in the northern Transvaal (today Limpopo). He died on April 19.